转过身笑一下 魁北瓜
Turn around and smile, Québécois.

190
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,300
早啊
Bonjour.

191
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:43,010
怎么了
?a va?

192
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:46,920
十点钟方向的德国军官 我认得他
The German officer at ten o'clock. I think I recognize him.

193
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:50,400
他是德国军情局马赛分局的人
He was attached to the Abwehr. In Marseille.

194
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:52,640
他审问过我
He interrogated me once.

195
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,660
他没看你 他在看报纸
He hasn't seen you. He's reading his paper.

196
00:20:05,670 --> 00:20:06,900
谢谢
Merci.

197
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:18,860
你肯定是他
You're sure that it's him?

198
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,410
对
Oui.

199
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:21,920
确定吗？
Really sure?

200
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,700
六成确定
60% sure.

201
00:20:51,450 --> 00:20:53,450
给我接维希政府警察局
Put me through to the Vichy Commissariat of Police.

202
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:54,690
快点
Quickly.

203
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:55,690
请你稍等
Please wait a moment

204
00:20:56,220 --> 00:20:57,300
好 我等着
Yes... I'll hold.

205
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,890
那儿好像有人噎着了
Sounds like somebody's choking back there.

206
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,170
好了 亲爱的
Okay, chérie.

207
00:21:56,010 --> 00:21:57,440
我们走吧
Mademoiselle.

208
00:21:57,740 --> 00:21:59,740
冒着雨赶了三个小时的路
The rain drove three hours of the road

209
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:01,240
我们终于到地儿了
We finally reached our destination

210
00:22:01,490 --> 00:22:02,790
可是眼前根本就不是
But it's not at all

211
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:05,240
他们跟我们描述过的漂亮的豪华建筑
The beautiful luxury buildings they described to us

212
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:06,660
而是一个小农场
It's a small farm

213
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:08,540
一片漆黑
Pitch black

214
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,040
我们已经准备回去了
We're ready to go back

215
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:11,710
这时一个穿着破旧的小个子男人出来了
Then a little man in shabby clothes came out

216
00:22:11,710 --> 00:22:12,540
他对我们说
He said to us

217
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:14,060
伯尔尼先生和太太
Mr. and Mrs. Bern

218
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,210
见我不太高兴
See I'm not happy

219
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,390
莫里斯就对我说
And Maurice said to me

220
00:22:17,110 --> 00:22:18,440
亲爱的 你要知道
Honey, you need to know

221
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,510
在人的回忆里
In the memory of man

222
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:20,940
什么东西都要比现实中大得多
Everything is much bigger than reality

223
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,020
莫里斯 我给你介绍个朋友 文森特
Maurice, meet my friend Vincent...

224
00:22:24,140 --> 00:22:25,920
…他也是巴黎人
...he's also from Paris.

225
00:22:27,990 --> 00:22:28,990
亲爱的
My love!

226
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:30,420
好无聊
I'm bored.

227
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:31,960
陪我跳舞
Dance with me.

228
00:22:32,530 --> 00:22:34,170
你真够疯的 伯尔尼夫人
You're utterly crazy, Madame Berne.

229
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:37,710
对啊 稍微疯狂一下感觉很好的
Yes. You could do with being a little crazy yourself.

230
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:46,680
真机灵
Well played.

231
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:48,620
小心那个人
Watch out for him.

232
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:56,650
那些家伙嫉妒得想杀了我
A lot of jealous guys giving me the evil eye.

233
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:02,300
那是因为他们知道我爱你
It's because they know I'm in love with you.

234
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:06,360
显而易见
It's very obvious.

235
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:21,960
嗯
Mmm.

236
00:23:28,630 --> 00:23:30,240
巴黎出什么事了
What went wrong in Paris?

237
00:23:32,570 --> 00:23:35,570
V部门撇下我们不管了
V Section left us hanging out to dry.

238
00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:38,280
你怎么逃掉的
How'd you get away?

239
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:40,880
我跑
I ran.

240
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,720
我跑 不停地跑
And ran, and kept on running.

241
00:24:01,770 --> 00:24:04,570
珀蒂夫人正在窗户后面看着我们
Madam Petit. Lurking in the window.

242
00:24:15,710 --> 00:24:17,020
晚安
Bonsoir.

243
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:40,710
跟我说说明天要见的
This Herr Hobar we're meeting tomorrow,

244
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:41,810
这位霍巴先生
what can you tell me about him?

245
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:44,580
他是大使的联络人
He's the Ambassador's liaison.

246
00:24:44,780 --> 00:24:46,980
来自科隆的纳粹高管
A high-ranking Party member from Cologne.

247
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:49,580
喜欢高尔夫和赌博
He likes golf and gambling.

248
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:51,720
他是我们最后的障碍
He's our final hurdle.

249
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:55,020
你有两秒钟
You have two seconds.

250
00:24:55,850 --> 00:24:56,920
开始
Go.

251
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:28,350
枪会贴在摆香槟的桌子下面
The guns will be taped under the champagne table.

252
00:25:28,950 --> 00:25:32,160
大使本人会在八点半准时到达
The Ambassador arrives at precisely 8:30.

253
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,230
他要是迟到呢
If he's late?

254
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:37,360
他是德国人 不会迟到的
He's German. He'll be on time.

255
00:25:38,260 --> 00:25:40,260
你怎么不会用斯特恩式轻机枪
How come you don't know Stens?

256
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,700
我会用轻机枪
I do know Stens.

257
00:25:43,940 --> 00:25:46,970
只是没看到你上了保险栓
I didn't see you set the travel safety.

258
00:25:47,770 --> 00:25:50,070
那你晚上用的机枪没问题吧
You'll be okay to use a Sten on the night, though?

259
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:53,950
需要的话我用餐具都没问题
I would be okay if I had to use cutlery.

260
00:25:58,920 --> 00:26:02,990
大使到达五分钟后 八点三十五分开始佯攻
The diversion attack will happen five minutes later at 8:35.

261
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:07,660
剩下的就都交给上帝了
And then everything will be in God's hands.

262
00:26:07,660 --> 00:26:08,730
很好
Good.

263
00:26:08,730 --> 00:26:11,860
希望他会用保险栓
Hopefully, he'll know how to work the safety.

264
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,010
好热
It's hot.

265
00:27:00,850 --> 00:27:02,250
你在干什么
What are you doing?

266
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,050
考验你
Testing you

267
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,790
就像你考验我一样
the way you tested me.

268
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:11,890
我知道你拿着武器 瓦坦先生
I know you are armed with a weapon, Mr. Vatan.

269
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:15,190
我只想看看你的保险栓上了没有
I'm just checking your safety catch is engaged.

270
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:21,330
看
There.

271
00:27:21,730 --> 00:27:23,800
我们第一次吵架
We had our first fight.

272
00:27:24,140 --> 00:27:26,200
现在又和好了 对吧
Now we're okay again, yes?

273
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:29,840
玛丽安
Marianne,

274
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:32,840
你知道有人跟搭档上了床
we both know people who've fucked each other.

275
00:27:32,850 --> 00:27:35,150
然后搞砸了任务死掉了
Then they fucked up, and now they're fucking dead.

276
00:27:35,450 --> 00:27:37,820
你真够直接的
Wow, that's a lot of fucks.

277
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:41,790
把你的扣子都扣好
Fasten your goddamn buttons.

278
00:27:52,870 --> 00:27:54,500
其实 马克斯
Actually, Max,

279
00:27:55,770 --> 00:28:00,440
他们的错并不是在这种情况下上床
the mistake people make in these situations isn't fucking.

280
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:02,910
而是相爱
It's feeling.

281
00:29:29,450 --> 00:29:30,690
等很久了吗
Have you been waiting long?

282
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:32,300
没
Non.

283
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,730
霍巴先生可以见你们了
Herr Hobarwill see you now.

284
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:00,930
谢谢
Oh, merci.

285
00:30:02,060 --> 00:30:03,160
不了
Non.

286
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:05,100
我丈夫正在戒烟
My husband's trying to cut down.

287
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:08,300
说是打起仗来大家都抽得太凶了
He says the war makes everyone smoke too much.

288
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:10,940
我只知道镇子上的人都在说他的好
I've only heard good things about him around town.

289
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:12,100
他的好
Good things.

290
00:30:13,310 --> 00:30:14,940
请坐 二位
Sit down, please.

291
00:30:19,610 --> 00:30:21,550
你丈夫不会说英语吗
Your husband doesn't speak English?

292
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:23,350
就会一点儿
Only a little.

293
00:30:25,230 --> 00:30:28,470
你妻子问我可不可以带你去参加大使馆的舞会
Your wife has asked if she could bring you to the Ambassador's Ball tomorrow.

294
00:30:28,910 --> 00:30:30,460
是这样…但是
Yes, but...

295
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:32,620
…不行的话我也能理解
...if it's a problem, I understand.

296
00:30:34,290 --> 00:30:36,360
他好像不太想去
He doesn't seem to want to come.

297
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:42,830
哦 瓦朗斯街那儿有场牌局
Oh.There is a stupid poker game in the Rue Valence.

298
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,140
明白了
I see.

299
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:48,210
你说了我什么？
What are you saying about me?

300
00:30:48,270 --> 00:30:51,010
别让我丢人 你一定要去 就这么定了
Don't embarrass me. You're coming and that's that.

301
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:53,280
你丈夫玩扑克吗
So, your husband plays poker?

302
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,610
他特别着迷
Oh, he's obsessed.

303
00:30:54,610 --> 00:30:56,950
我也是 我也是
As am I. As am I.

304
00:30:56,950 --> 00:30:59,350
现在切牌 大牌赢
And now we cut. High card wins.

305
00:31:00,490 --> 00:31:02,020
赢什么
Wins what?

306
00:31:02,020 --> 00:31:03,350
要是他的牌大
If his card is higher than mine,

307
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,960
他就可以去打牌了
he can go to his poker game.

308
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,160
不然的话 就必须参加宴会
If it's lower, he must come to the party.

309
00:31:08,390 --> 00:31:11,100
这也太荒唐了
This is too absurd.

310
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:14,460
洗牌吧 先生
Shuffle, Mr. Berne.

311
00:31:16,850 --> 00:31:18,640
谁牌大谁赢
High card wins.

312
00:31:35,450 --> 00:31:36,520
他是采矿的
Mining?

313
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:38,590
对
Yes.

314
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:46,260
是开采磷矿的 对吧
He works with phosphate, right?

315
00:31:46,270 --> 00:31:47,530
没错
That's right.

316
00:31:58,870 --> 00:32:01,920
切牌吧 伯尔尼先生 为了你的自由
Now cut, Mr. Berne. For your freedom.

317
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,380
真遗憾
Too bad.

318
00:32:31,420 --> 00:32:33,370
这下你玩不了牌了
No pokerforyou.

319
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:40,790
谢谢
Merci.

320
00:32:42,550 --> 00:32:44,120
- 谢谢  - 告辞
- Merci.  - Au revoir.

321
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:46,360
呃
Ah. Uh...

322
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,830
还有一件事 新发的邀请函
One more thing. Boring. Procedure.

323
00:32:49,230 --> 00:32:50,690
要走个无聊的小程序
For new names on the list.

324
00:32:52,530 --> 00:32:53,670
伯尔尼先生
Mr. Berne...

325
00:32:54,010 --> 00:32:57,590
请在这里写下磷酸盐的化学式
...write down the chemical formula for phosphate, please.

326
00:33:40,110 --> 00:33:41,710
我们明天见
See you both tomorrow.

327
00:33:45,820 --> 00:33:47,750
快要开始了
So, it's in the cards.

328
00:33:48,420 --> 00:33:50,750
我们有机会名留青史了
We get our chance to make history.

329
00:33:59,730 --> 00:34:01,330
我睡不着
I couldn't sleep.

330
00:34:01,330 --> 00:34:02,400
嗯
Mmm.

331
00:34:05,800 --> 00:34:08,740
我不会让你失望的 魁北瓜
I won't let you down, Le Québécois.

332
00:34:10,680 --> 00:34:11,840
我知道
I know.

333
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:20,420
我们出去吧 去看日出
Let's get out of here. Let's go watch the sunrise.

334
00:34:29,290 --> 00:34:30,830
有多大几率
What are our odds?

335
00:34:31,230 --> 00:34:32,560
活下来吗
Of surviving?

336
00:34:32,760 --> 00:34:34,370
六四开
60-40.

337
00:34:34,730 --> 00:34:36,270
六成死
Against.

338
00:34:37,570 --> 00:34:39,400
两个人都活下来的几率更小
Both of us, I don't know.

339
00:34:43,180 --> 00:34:45,540
跟我说说梅迪辛哈特吧
So, tell me about Medicine Hat.

340
00:34:49,750 --> 00:34:53,620
遍地绿色 山丘起伏 水流清澈
Pretty green. Rolling hills. Clear water.

341
00:34:55,220 --> 00:34:57,620
事情变得糟糕时 我就会想起那里
Just a place I go when things get dark.

342
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:00,560
你呢
You?

343
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,890
你想去哪儿
You have a place?

344
00:35:04,300 --> 00:35:06,360
等仗打完了
When the war is over,

345
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:08,970
我在哪儿都无所谓
it won't matter where I am.

346
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,550
我们该走了
We should be going.

347
00:35:51,410 --> 00:35:53,480
要是我们明天死了
If we're dead tomorrow,

348
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:59,320
没人会知道
no one would know.

349
00:37:59,590 --> 00:38:01,160
你看起来真美
You look beautiful.

350
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:04,040
枪呢
The guns?

351
00:38:04,380 --> 00:38:05,710
处理了
Gone.

352
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:07,710
很好
Bien.

353
00:38:08,550 --> 00:38:10,380
谢谢 魁北瓜
Merci, Le Québécois.

354
00:38:11,380 --> 00:38:13,120
我是安大略人
I'm from Ontario.

355
00:38:19,520 --> 00:38:20,860
谢谢
Merci.

356
00:38:22,880 --> 00:38:24,420
八点三十二了
It's 8:32.

357
00:38:24,780 --> 00:38:26,630
离佯攻还有三分钟
Three minutes until the diversion.

358
00:38:37,540 --> 00:38:40,530
我发现这种时候想点搞笑的事能放松神经
In this kind of situation, I find it useful to think about something funny.

359
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:45,830
笑一下或者说句话
Smile or something.

360
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:49,670
你看起来很美
You look beautiful.

361
00:38:51,470 --> 00:38:52,580
这句说过了
You already told me that.

362
00:38:53,690 --> 00:38:54,760
是吗
Quoi?

363
00:38:56,660 --> 00:38:57,780
能正眼看我吗
Can you even see me?

364
00:39:00,450 --> 00:39:01,590
不能
Not really.

365
00:39:24,250 --> 00:39:26,210
- 啊 你们俩  - 晚上好
- Ah. You two.  - Good evening.

366
00:39:26,620 --> 00:39:27,800
晚上好 你好吗
Good evening. How are you?

367
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:29,830
很好 谢谢 你呢？
Very well, thank you. And you?

368
00:39:30,180 --> 00:39:31,180
还行
Not bad.

369
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,000
那么…
So...?

370
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:37,940
宴会…很有意思
So... It's lovely.

371
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:39,170
嗯
Mmm.

372
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,170
希特勒万岁
Heil Hitler.

373
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:51,500
他迟到了
He's late.

374
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:56,500
他在干什么？
What's he doing?

375
00:40:28,700 --> 00:40:30,600
女士们 先生们
Ladies and gentlemen

376
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:32,700
党员同志们
Party comrades

377
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:35,200
德国和法国
Germany and France

378
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:40,700
这两个伟大的国家之间的联盟提醒着我们
The alliance between the two great nations reminds us

379
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:46,300
我们正处在一场非常艰巨的战争之中
We are in a very difficult war

380
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:50,100
仅仅在过去这短短的一年
Only in the past year

381
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:39,890
走
Move!

382
00:42:31,940 --> 00:42:33,780
没有人追我们
No one's following us.

383
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:42,420
我们活下来了 马克斯 我们俩都活下来了
We're alive, Max. We're both alive.

384
00:42:45,660 --> 00:42:46,990
跟我去伦敦
Come with me to London.

385
00:42:51,660 --> 00:42:53,760
跟我去伦敦 然后嫁给我
Come with me to London and be my wife.

386
00:43:12,500 --> 00:43:15,500
[三个星期后]

